Dilmah is Sri Lanka's most recognised international brand of tea. The company was founded in 1974 by Merrill J Fernando. The name Dilmah was chosen by combining the first names of Fernando's sons Dilhan and Malik. It is available in over 100 countries including Estonia, the United Kingdom, Turkey, Lithuania, Pakistan, Poland, Russia, Hungary, Canada, Chile, South Africa, Australia, Indonesia, Japan, the United States and New Zealand. In 2009 it was considered that Dilmah was the sixth-largest tea brand in the world.
